The paper presents an algorithm for constructing the compacted de Bruijn graph from a set of complete genomes, which is a data structure used in genomic analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the biological applications of the algorithm, indicating that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.BIO (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics). The algorithm is designed to be low memory and scalable, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also mentions that the algorithm could enable novel biological analyses, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the algorithm involves statistical analysis, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
